The paper deals with face recognition, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed regularized robust coding (RRC) method involves regression and optimization, which are also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments involve face databases, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper mentions the computational cost of the sparse representation based classification (SRC) method, which could relate to information theory (cs.IT).
